      <h3 class="post-title">First post — My first small project</h3>
      <div class="meta">Posted on 2026-01-26</div>

      <div class="post-body">
        <p>Today I finished a tiny web app that displays quotes. It was my first time wiring up HTML, CSS, and a little JavaScript. I practiced structuring the page with <span class="highlight">semantic elements</span> like <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, and I used CSS to make the text readable.</p>

        <p>Key takeaways:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Start small — build a minimal version first.</li>
          <li>Use clear headings and readable fonts (I used a serif for titles and a system sans-serif for body text).</li>
          <li>Keep line-height comfortable for long paragraphs.</li>
        </ul>

