    <article id="post-2">
      <h3 class="post-title">Second post — What I learned this week</h3>
      <div class="meta">Posted on 2026-01-20</div>

      <div class="post-body">
        <p>This week I focused on CSS text properties. I experimented with <strong>font-family</strong>, <strong>line-height</strong>, and <strong>font-style</strong> to improve readability. I also learned how to provide fallback fonts like <code>font-family: "Courier New", monospace;</code> for code snippets.</p>

        <p>Example improvements I made:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Increased <em>line-height</em> to 1.6 for body text so paragraphs breathe.</li>
          <li>Used a monospace font for small code examples to keep alignment consistent.</li>
          <li>Styled dates with <code>font-style: italic;</code> to visually separate metadata from content.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>Next steps: add a simple archive page and let readers filter posts by tag.</p>

        <a class="back-to-top" href="#top">Back to top</a>
      </div>
